      },
      "date": "2014-10-01 14:50:20.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(8 comments)\n\nThis has a lot of magic constants (6, 9, 20, 30, 32, 60) for the wait times. The most informative thing about them I could fine was this comment repeated a few times in sanity-lfsck.sh:\n\n \n# The LFSCK status query internal is 30 seconds. For the case\n# of some LFSCK_NOTIFY RPCs failure/lost, we will wait enough\n# time to guarantee the status sync up.\n\nIt would be good to have comments that explained each wait time. It would better to have named constants for each of them.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
