        "subject": "LU-5301 tests: increase timeout for sanity-lfsck tests",
        "message": "LU-5301 tests: increase timeout for sanity-lfsck tests\n\nIncrease the time waited for sanity-lfsck tests for LFSCK to complete\nor perform some action.  When running in VMs or with different\nfilesystems, the time taken by LFSCK stages can vary noticeably.\nUse wait_timeout_facet() so that the wait is as short as possible.\n\nConsolidate repeated commands to get the LFSCK status for ease of\nreading the tests.\n\nUpdate wait_update() to follow proper coding style (lower-case local\nvariables, avoid name clashes with bash builtins), and add a new\ncomment block for it.  Add argument handling to wait_update_facet().\n\nRemove redundant calls to clear fail_loc at the end of a test, since\nthis is done in run_one() after every test.\n\nTest-Parameters: alwaysuploadlogs envdefinitions=SLOW=yes \ttestlist=lfsck-performance\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Ia42ba28ba5e60f7c127fa930d9025244a5500c1e\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
